Adult/immature.description: Song Sparrows and Fox Sparrows both vary extensively across their range. Song Sparrows have a grayish bill, a stripe through the eye, and coarse streaks instead of spots on the breast.

Adult (Savannah).description: Savannah Sparrows are smaller than Fox Sparrows and have smaller bills and shorter tails. They are more finely streaked and usually have yellow above the eye.
